wikipedia_page.main: Audrey Hancock (28 February 1919 – 21 October 2017) was a British swimmer. She competed in women's 100 metre backstroke at the 1936 Summer Olympics. She also competed at the 1934 British Empire Games and was the amateur backstroke lady champion of the Midlands.
